{"markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"","page-layout":"full"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n```{=html}\n<div style=\"background: linear-gradient(135deg,#0d2b45,#1a4a6e); color:white; padding:1rem 1rem 1rem;\">\n  <div style=\"max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;\">\n    <h1 style=\"font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; font-size:2.4rem; margin-bottom:0.4rem;\">Research</h1>\n    <p style=\"color:#c8d8e8; font-size:1rem; max-width:600px;\">\n<p style=\"color:#c8d8e8; font-size:1rem; max-width:700px;\">\n      High-resolution climate modeling · Cryosphere dynamics · Glacier mass balance · Permafrost · High mountain hydroclimate · Heatwaves · Human-climate interactions in High Mountain Asia and the contiguous United States\n    </p>\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<section class=\"section\" style=\"background:white;\">\n  <div style=\"max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;\">\n\n    <!-- PhD Dissertation -->\n    <div class=\"section-title\">Ph.D. Dissertation Work</div>\n    <br/>\n    <div style=\"background:#f0f6fb; border-radius:8px; padding:1.8rem 2rem; margin-bottom:2rem; border-left:4px solid #1a4a6e;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; color:#1a4a6e; font-size:1.3rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem;\">\n        High-Resolution Climate Simulations and Impacts of Local Human Factors on Hydroclimate and Glacier Dynamics in High Mountain Asia\n      </h3>\n      <p style=\"color:#4a5568; font-size:0.93rem; line-height:1.75;\">\n        My dissertation examines how large-scale irrigation across South Asia perturbs the regional hydroclimate system and remote glacier dynamics in the Himalaya and Karakoram, using high-resolution WRF regional climate models.\n      </p>\n      <p style=\"margin-top:0.4rem; font-size:0.88rem; color:#2e86ab; font-weight:600;\">\n        University of Nebraska-Lincoln · Expected Summer 2026\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n    <!-- Ongoing Work -->\n    <div style=\"background:#fff8e7; border-left:4px solid #c9a84c; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0; padding:1.2rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom:2rem;\">\n      <p style=\"font-size:0.92rem; color:#4a5568; margin:0;\">\n        🔬 <strong>Ongoing Work:</strong> Two active projects investigate how irrigation-driven climate changes propagate into moisture transport across South Asia and glacier mass balance in High Mountain Asia. Figures and preliminary results are highlighted on the <a href=\"index.html\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-weight:600;\">Home page →</a>\n      </p>\n    </div>\n    <!-- Published: Climate Dynamics -->\n    <div class=\"pub-item\" style=\"margin-bottom:1.5rem;\">\n      <div class=\"pub-title\">Evaluating the Performance of High-Resolution Climate Simulations over the Central Himalaya and Karakoram</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-authors\"><strong>Gurung, T.R.</strong>, Chen, L., Ali, S.H., Rowe, C., Arriola, F.M. and Ritzema, R.S.</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-journal\">Climate Dynamics, 64(3), p.120 · 2026</div>\n      <p style=\"color:#4a5568; font-size:0.88rem; line-height:1.65; margin-top:0.5rem;\">\n        This study benchmarks WRF simulations against observations across the complex terrain of the Central Himalaya and Karakoram, evaluating their skill in reproducing temperature, precipitation, and atmospheric circulation — a critical step before using these models for impact studies.\n      </p>\n      <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/s00382-025-08030-x\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">DOI: 10.1007/s00382-025-08030-x →</a>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Published: ERL Heatwaves -->\n    <div class=\"pub-item\" style=\"margin-bottom:3rem;\">\n      <div class=\"pub-title\">Understanding the Influence of Soil Moisture on Heatwave Characteristics in the Contiguous United States</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-authors\"><strong>Gurung, T.R.</strong> and Chen, L.</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-journal\">Environmental Research Letters, 19(6) · 2024</div>\n      <p style=\"color:#4a5568; font-size:0.88rem; line-height:1.65; margin-top:0.5rem;\">\n        Using observational data and model simulations, this paper quantifies how antecedent soil moisture deficits amplify heatwave intensity, duration, and spatial extent across the contiguous US — highlighting land-atmosphere feedbacks as a key driver of extreme heat events.\n      </p>\n      <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1088/1748-9326/ad4dbb\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">DOI: 10.1088/1748-9326/ad4dbb →</a>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Earlier Work -->\n    <div class=\"section-title\">Earlier Research</div>\n    <br/>\n    <div style=\"display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(260px,1fr)); gap:1.2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;\">\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Glaciology</span>\n          <h3>Glacier Mass Balance — Rikha Samba</h3>\n          <p>Long-term mass balance reconstruction (1974–2021) and a decade of in-situ measurements at Rikha Samba Glacier, central Himalaya, using an energy-mass balance model.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1017/jog.2022.93\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Journal of Glaciology →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Glaciology</span>\n          <h3>Mass Balances — Yala &amp; Rikha Samba</h3>\n          <p>Geodetic and glaciological mass balance records (2000–2017) for Yala and Rikha Samba glaciers, providing a long-term dataset for the Nepal Himalaya.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5194/essd-13-3791-2021\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Earth System Science Data →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Cryosphere</span><span class=\"tag\">Permafrost</span>\n          <h3>Permafrost Change in High Mountain Asia</h3>\n          <p>A comprehensive review of climate change impacts and adaptation strategies related to permafrost dynamics across High Mountain Asia.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1088/1748-9326/acf1b4\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Environ. Res. Letters →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Hydroclimate</span><span class=\"tag\">Langtang</span>\n          <h3>High Mountain Water Cycle — Langtang</h3>\n          <p>Multi-year observations of the water cycle in the Langtang catchment, Central Himalaya, documenting precipitation, snowmelt, and streamflow dynamics.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1002/hyp.14189\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Hydrological Processes →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <p style=\"margin-top:1rem;\">\n      <a href=\"publications.html\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-weight:600;\">See all publications →</a>\n    </p>\n\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<footer class=\"site-footer\">\n  <p>© 2026 Tika Ram Gurung · University of Nebraska-Lincoln</p>\n</footer>\n` ``\n```","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n```{=html}\n<div style=\"background: linear-gradient(135deg,#0d2b45,#1a4a6e); color:white; padding:1rem 1rem 1rem;\">\n  <div style=\"max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;\">\n    <h1 style=\"font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; font-size:2.4rem; margin-bottom:0.4rem;\">Research</h1>\n    <p style=\"color:#c8d8e8; font-size:1rem; max-width:600px;\">\n<p style=\"color:#c8d8e8; font-size:1rem; max-width:700px;\">\n      High-resolution climate modeling · Cryosphere dynamics · Glacier mass balance · Permafrost · High mountain hydroclimate · Heatwaves · Human-climate interactions in High Mountain Asia and the contiguous United States\n    </p>\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<section class=\"section\" style=\"background:white;\">\n  <div style=\"max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;\">\n\n    <!-- PhD Dissertation -->\n    <div class=\"section-title\">Ph.D. Dissertation Work</div>\n    <br/>\n    <div style=\"background:#f0f6fb; border-radius:8px; padding:1.8rem 2rem; margin-bottom:2rem; border-left:4px solid #1a4a6e;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; color:#1a4a6e; font-size:1.3rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem;\">\n        High-Resolution Climate Simulations and Impacts of Local Human Factors on Hydroclimate and Glacier Dynamics in High Mountain Asia\n      </h3>\n      <p style=\"color:#4a5568; font-size:0.93rem; line-height:1.75;\">\n        My dissertation examines how large-scale irrigation across South Asia perturbs the regional hydroclimate system and remote glacier dynamics in the Himalaya and Karakoram, using high-resolution WRF regional climate models.\n      </p>\n      <p style=\"margin-top:0.4rem; font-size:0.88rem; color:#2e86ab; font-weight:600;\">\n        University of Nebraska-Lincoln · Expected Summer 2026\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n    <!-- Ongoing Work -->\n    <div style=\"background:#fff8e7; border-left:4px solid #c9a84c; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0; padding:1.2rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom:2rem;\">\n      <p style=\"font-size:0.92rem; color:#4a5568; margin:0;\">\n        🔬 <strong>Ongoing Work:</strong> Two active projects investigate how irrigation-driven climate changes propagate into moisture transport across South Asia and glacier mass balance in High Mountain Asia. Figures and preliminary results are highlighted on the <a href=\"index.html\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-weight:600;\">Home page →</a>\n      </p>\n    </div>\n    <!-- Published: Climate Dynamics -->\n    <div class=\"pub-item\" style=\"margin-bottom:1.5rem;\">\n      <div class=\"pub-title\">Evaluating the Performance of High-Resolution Climate Simulations over the Central Himalaya and Karakoram</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-authors\"><strong>Gurung, T.R.</strong>, Chen, L., Ali, S.H., Rowe, C., Arriola, F.M. and Ritzema, R.S.</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-journal\">Climate Dynamics, 64(3), p.120 · 2026</div>\n      <p style=\"color:#4a5568; font-size:0.88rem; line-height:1.65; margin-top:0.5rem;\">\n        This study benchmarks WRF simulations against observations across the complex terrain of the Central Himalaya and Karakoram, evaluating their skill in reproducing temperature, precipitation, and atmospheric circulation — a critical step before using these models for impact studies.\n      </p>\n      <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/s00382-025-08030-x\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">DOI: 10.1007/s00382-025-08030-x →</a>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Published: ERL Heatwaves -->\n    <div class=\"pub-item\" style=\"margin-bottom:3rem;\">\n      <div class=\"pub-title\">Understanding the Influence of Soil Moisture on Heatwave Characteristics in the Contiguous United States</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-authors\"><strong>Gurung, T.R.</strong> and Chen, L.</div>\n      <div class=\"pub-journal\">Environmental Research Letters, 19(6) · 2024</div>\n      <p style=\"color:#4a5568; font-size:0.88rem; line-height:1.65; margin-top:0.5rem;\">\n        Using observational data and model simulations, this paper quantifies how antecedent soil moisture deficits amplify heatwave intensity, duration, and spatial extent across the contiguous US — highlighting land-atmosphere feedbacks as a key driver of extreme heat events.\n      </p>\n      <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1088/1748-9326/ad4dbb\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">DOI: 10.1088/1748-9326/ad4dbb →</a>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Earlier Work -->\n    <div class=\"section-title\">Earlier Research</div>\n    <br/>\n    <div style=\"display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(260px,1fr)); gap:1.2rem; margin-bottom:2rem;\">\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Glaciology</span>\n          <h3>Glacier Mass Balance — Rikha Samba</h3>\n          <p>Long-term mass balance reconstruction (1974–2021) and a decade of in-situ measurements at Rikha Samba Glacier, central Himalaya, using an energy-mass balance model.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1017/jog.2022.93\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Journal of Glaciology →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Glaciology</span>\n          <h3>Mass Balances — Yala &amp; Rikha Samba</h3>\n          <p>Geodetic and glaciological mass balance records (2000–2017) for Yala and Rikha Samba glaciers, providing a long-term dataset for the Nepal Himalaya.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5194/essd-13-3791-2021\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Earth System Science Data →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Cryosphere</span><span class=\"tag\">Permafrost</span>\n          <h3>Permafrost Change in High Mountain Asia</h3>\n          <p>A comprehensive review of climate change impacts and adaptation strategies related to permafrost dynamics across High Mountain Asia.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1088/1748-9326/acf1b4\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Environ. Res. Letters →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"project-card\">\n        <div class=\"project-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"tag\">Hydroclimate</span><span class=\"tag\">Langtang</span>\n          <h3>High Mountain Water Cycle — Langtang</h3>\n          <p>Multi-year observations of the water cycle in the Langtang catchment, Central Himalaya, documenting precipitation, snowmelt, and streamflow dynamics.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1002/hyp.14189\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;\">Hydrological Processes →</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <p style=\"margin-top:1rem;\">\n      <a href=\"publications.html\" style=\"color:#2e86ab; font-weight:600;\">See all publications →</a>\n    </p>\n\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<footer class=\"site-footer\">\n  <p>© 2026 Tika Ram Gurung · University of Nebraska-Lincoln</p>\n</footer>\n` ``\n```"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","css":[